FISH (Pros. Attorney) vs. STOCKDALE (Justice of the Peace), No. 15520; 3 D. L. N., 577; 69 N. W., 92.

(Certiorari to Allegan.)

To compel a justice of the peace to issue a warrant upon a complaint made under Act No. 186, v Laws -of 1893, relative to taking and catching fish' in inland waters, the circuit judge having determined that the Act was unconstitutional because of defective title.

Affirmed and'writ denied December 4, 1896.
